==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deodar
<hw>De`o*dar"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native name, fr.
Skr. <ets>d⟦emac⟧vad⟦amac⟧ru</ets>, prop., timber of the gods.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A kind of cedar (<spn>Cedrus Deodara</spn>),
growing in India, highly valued for its size and beauty as well as for
its timber, and also grown in England as an ornamental tree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deodate</ent>⟦br⟧
